PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773288217
OL,3,CTim Davie says trust in institutions
OL,4,Clike BBC in 'full on crisis'
OL,6,FPublic trust in institutions such as
OL,7,Fthe BBC is in "full on crisis," the
OL,8,Fcorporation's outgoing director-
OL,9,Fgeneral Tim Davie has warned.
OL,11,FSpeaking on The Rest Is Entertainment
OL,12,Fpodcast, Mr Davie also acknowledged
OL,13,Fthat the BBC has made some "serious
OL,14,Fmistakes, which we regret".
OL,16,FHis appearance as a guest on the
OL,17,Fpodcast comes as he prepares to step
OL,18,Fdown from his position next month
OL,19,Fafter resigning following a series of
OL,20,Fscandals at the BBC.
OL,26,@oD@OOUoD@_O]uD@\OUvD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773288217
OL,3,CTim Davie says trust in institutions
OL,4,Clike BBC in 'full on crisis'
OL,6,FLast summer the corporation faced
OL,7,Fcriticism for its live broadcast of
OL,8,Fpunk duo Bob Vylan's Glastonbury
OL,9,FFestival set, as the group led chants
OL,10,Fof "death, death to the IDF (Israel
OL,11,FDefence Forces)" during their
OL,12,Fperformance.
OL,14,FAnd in November it emerged that the
OL,15,FBBC selectively edited a speech made
OL,16,Fby Donald Trump on the day of the US
OL,17,FCapitol attack for a Panorama
OL,18,Fdocumentary.
OL,26,@rD@DOUsD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773288217
OL,3,CTim Davie says trust in institutions
OL,4,Clike BBC in 'full on crisis'
OL,6,FMr Davie told the podcast's hosts,
OL,7,FRichard Osman and Marina Hyde: "We
OL,8,Fhave a crisis.
OL,10,F"It is ` we should call it ` a full-on
OL,11,Fcrisis that people do not trust too
OL,12,Fmany of our institutions.
OL,14,F"And in the UK, we're well ahead of
OL,15,Fthe world. We hate to even be happy
OL,16,Fabout things, but it is a wonder that
OL,17,Fwe have these institutions and they're
OL,18,Fthere to serve.
OL,26,@oD@`OUrD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773288217
OL,3,CTim Davie says trust in institutions
OL,4,Clike BBC in 'full on crisis'
OL,6,F"But trust is built and I'm semi-
OL,7,Fobsessed by this ` trust is built by
OL,8,Fpeople absolutely believing that
OL,9,Fsomeone is acting in their interest
OL,10,Fand that they listen to them."
OL,12,FMr Davie, who will be replaced by
OL,13,FRhodri Talfan Davies as the
OL,14,Fcorporation's interim director-general
OL,15,Ffrom April 3, also said the BBC is
OL,16,Foperating in a "weaponisation" era.
OL,18,F"We're in an age where weaponisation
OL,19,Fis rife," Mr Davie told the podcast.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@^O]xD@POUxD@^O]zD@AOU{D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773288217
OL,3,CTim Davie says trust in institutions
OL,4,Clike BBC in 'full on crisis'
OL,6,F"And when I say weaponisation, someone
OL,7,Fsaid to me, well it's not
OL,8,Fweaponisation, it's simply pointing
OL,9,Fout the fact that you didn't get that
OL,10,Fright or you pulled that documentary.
OL,12,F"And that is true. We've made
OL,13,Fmistakes, sometimes serious mistakes,
OL,14,Fwhich we regret. But weaponisation is
OL,15,Fselectively taking one fact ` it may
OL,16,Fbe a fact, so you're standing on a
OL,17,Ffact ` but what you're not standing on
OL,18,Fis any effort to be proportionate.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773288217
OL,3,CTim Davie says trust in institutions
OL,4,Clike BBC in 'full on crisis'
OL,6,F"You're not saying, look, a thousand
OL,7,Fstories run, we're running, and one
OL,8,Fdidn't get it right, or overall this
OL,9,Fis where there's no balance of data.
OL,10,FIt's literally just selecting a fact
OL,11,Fto make a case."
OL,13,FMr Davie, who became director-general
OL,14,Fin September 2020, said he was in no
OL,15,Fdoubt that the BBC will continue to
OL,16,Fexist, but the question is whether or
OL,17,Fnot it will be a "market failure `
OL,18,Fforgive the jargon".
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@PO]yD@ROUzD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773288217
OL,3,CTim Davie says trust in institutions
OL,4,Clike BBC in 'full on crisis'
OL,6,F"Almost a charity project on the side
OL,7,Ffunded by general taxation or whatever
OL,8,Fit is where people don't feel
OL,9,Fparticipative," he added.
OL,11,F"I mean the DG may resign or something
OL,12,Fbig might happen but if you've got two
OL,13,Fout of four TV channels you have to be
OL,14,Fdoing a pretty poor job not to get an
OL,15,Faudience and I think what I've tried
OL,16,Fto do in my tenure is say: let's not
OL,17,Fworry too much about that ` let's
OL,18,Freally worry about the value."
OL,20,FBut he said the BBC does not simply
OL,21,Fhave a "right to exist".
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@OO]sD@AOUzD@^O]}D@HOU}D@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773288217
OL,3,CTim Davie says trust in institutions
OL,4,Clike BBC in 'full on crisis'
OL,6,F"It has to absolutely deliver value to
OL,7,Fevery household," he added.
OL,9,FMr Davie also spoke on the topic of
OL,10,Fthe BBC charter renewal, which takes
OL,11,Fplace around every 10 years and is due
OL,12,Fto expire in December 2027.
OL,14,F"The point is not whether the BBC
OL,15,Fexists or not, it's how that happens,"
OL,16,Fhe told the podcast.
OL,18,F"And the idea that you've got a
OL,19,Fpassive action to not renew just
OL,20,Fallows us to drift off ` to me that
OL,21,Fjust doesn't make sense."
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@QO]vD@AOUwD@fO]zD@AOU}D@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773288217
OL,3,CTim Davie says trust in institutions
OL,4,Clike BBC in 'full on crisis'
OL,6,FHe said this often gets misunderstood
OL,7,Fas the BBC not wanting accountability,
OL,8,Fadding: "Nothing could be further than
OL,9,Fthe truth ` we need accountability.
OL,11,F"But I do think the idea of a basic
OL,12,Flevel of charter ` I don't know, there
OL,13,Fmight be an example out there ` but an
OL,14,Foverall charter that has a time length
OL,15,Flike this, I think there should be a
OL,16,Fstandard provision that just goes
OL,17,Fforever, basically, until Parliament,
OL,18,For whatever the mechanism is, decides
OL,19,Fthrough recent debate ` actively,
OL,20,Factively, not passively ` to say,
OL,21,Fokay, we don't want the BBC anymore."
OL,26,@pD@IOUsD@AOU}D@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
